       fhir:v "This value set contains a point-in-time expansion enumerating the codes that meet the value set intent. As new versions of the code systems used by the value set are released, the contents of this expansion will need to be updated to incorporate newly defined codes that meet the value set intent. Before, and periodically during production use, the value set expansion contents SHOULD be updated. The value set expansion specifies the timestamp when the expansion was produced, SHOULD contain the parameters used for the expansion, and SHALL contain the codes that are obtained by evaluating the value set definition. If this is ONLY an executable value set, a distributable definition of the value set must be obtained to compute the updated expansion."
     ]
  ] [
     fhir:url [
       fhir:v "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/valueset-rules-text"^^xsd:anyURI ;
       fhir:l <http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/valueset-rules-text>
     ] ;
     fhir:value [
       a fhir:Markdown ;
       fhir:v "https://mor.nlm.nih.gov/RxMix/ Script:\r\nStep 1a \r\nCreate Batch text input file (CNSD.txt) with following DailyMed identifier (for the concept \"Central Nervous System Depressants\") as an input within the file: \r\nN0000175728       \r\n\r\nStep 1b\r\nSubmit batch job using the above CNSD.txt file to following workflow by uploading file (CNSD-wf.config) with the following in the file:  <WFE><filteredOutputs>RXCUI|name|term_type</filteredOutputs><input>NOINPUT</input><FS><service>NOINPUT</service><function>getClassMembers</function><level>0</level><paramSize>5</paramSize><param order ='0'>?</param><param order ='1'>DAILYMED</param><param order ='2'>N/A</param><param order ='3'>0</param><param order ='4'>IN,MIN,PIN</param></FS><FS><service>NOINPUT</service><function>getRelatedByType</function><level>1</level><paramSize>2</paramSize><param order ='0'>?</param><param order ='1'>BPCK,GPCK,SBD,SCD</param></FS></WFE>\r\nStep 2\r\nTo remove all cough and bowel transit formulation codes and to remove the injectable codes filter out all codes with the following strings:\r\nIngredient strings: \r\nGuaifenesin, Chlorpheniramine, Pseudoephedrine, Brompheniramine, Phenylephrine, Phenylpropanolamine, Promethazine, Bromodiphenhydramine, guaiacolsulfonate, homatropine\r\nForm strings:\r\ninject, cartridge, syringe"
     ]
  ] ) ; # 
  fhir:url [
     fhir:v "http://fhir.org/guides/cdc/opioid-cds/ValueSet/cns-depressant-medications"^^xsd:anyURI ;
     fhir:l <http://fhir.org/guides/cdc/opioid-cds/ValueSet/cns-depressant-medications>
  ] ; # 
  fhir:version [ fhir:v "2022.1.0"] ; # 
  fhir:name [ fhir:v "CNS_DEPRESSANT_MEDICATIONS"] ; # 
  fhir:title [ fhir:v "CNS depressant medications"] ; # 
  fhir:status [ fhir:v "active"] ; # 
  fhir:experimental [ fhir:v false] ; # 
  fhir:date [ fhir:v "2025-02-24T13:06:43-07:00"^^xsd:dateTime] ; # 
  fhir:publisher [ fhir:v "CDC / Security Risk Solutions, Inc. (SRS)"] ; # 
  fhir:contact ( [
     fhir:telecom ( [
       fhir:system [ fhir:v "url" ] ;
       fhir:value [ fhir:v "https://www.securityrisksolutions.com" ]
     ] )
  ] ) ; # 
  fhir:description [ fhir:v "Medications considered to have an ingredient considered to be a CNS depressant, some of which may be mild. Removed from this set are cough medications and bowl transit modifiers."] ; # 
  fhir:copyright [ fhir:v "© CDC 2016+."] ; # 
